==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erased
<hw>E*rased"</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧st")</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Rubbed or scraped out; effaced; obliterated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Represented with jagged and uneven
edges, as is torn off; -- used esp. of the head or limb of a beast. Cf.
<er>Couped</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erasement</ent>⟦br⟧
